title: vaccineff
text: cohort design VE estimated using Hazard Ratios (\(HR\)) vaccinated unvaccinated populations according following equation: \[VE = (1-HR(t))\times100\] HR estimated using Cox Proportional Hazards model: \[h_g(t,s)=h_{0,g}\exp(\beta s)\] hazards modeled terms status vaccination. proportional hazards hypothesis checked using Shoenfled test. hypothesis satisfied, recommended stratify population smaller groups (g) using confounding variables.

previous_headings: For which designs of vaccine effectiveness is this package?
title: vaccineff
text: test negative design modified case-control design. vaccinfe effectiveness estimated using odds ratio () vaccination among cases divided vaccination among controls. \[VE = 1- \frac{\text{Vaccination among cases}}{\text{Vaccination among controls}}\times 100\]

previous_headings: For which designs of vaccine effectiveness is this package?
title: vaccineff
text: screening method estimates VE using proportion cases vaccinated (PCV) proportion population vaccinated (PPV) using following expression: \[VE = \frac{\text{PCV}}{1-\text{PCV}} \times \frac{1-\text{PPV}}{\text{PPV}} \times 100\] calculate PCV, supposed , least, random sample cases disease arising given period defined population available. Additionally, takes PPV prior information external estimate.

text: current release package bases estimation cohort design VE hypothesis proportional hazards vaccinated unvaccinated populations. estimation hazard ratio relies implementation Cox model R package: survival integrated data set cohortdata provides minimal example input package. following code can used prepare data set model implementation implements basic constant model:
code: data("cohortdata")  cohortdata$immunization_death <-   get_immunization_date(data = cohortdata,                         outcome_date_col = "death_date",                         outcome_delay = 0,                         immunization_delay = 14,                         vacc_date_col = c("vaccine_date_1", "vaccine_date_2"),                         end_cohort = "2021-12-31",                         take_first = FALSE)  cohortdata$vaccine_status <- set_status(data = cohortdata,                                         col_names = "immunization_death",                                         status = c("v", "u"))  cohortdata$death_status <- set_status(data = cohortdata,                                       col_names = "death_date")  cohortdata$time_to_death <- get_time_to_event(data = cohortdata,                                               outcome_date_col = "death_date",                                               start_cohort = "2021-01-01",                                               end_cohort =  "2021-12-31",                                               start_from_immunization = FALSE)  coh_eff_noconf(data = cohortdata,                outcome_status_col = "death_status",                time_to_event_col = "time_to_death",                status_vacc_col = "vaccine_status") #>                              HR HR_low HR_high  V_eff V_eff_low V_eff_high #> data[[status_vacc_col]]v 0.3289 0.1732  0.6247 0.6711    0.3753     0.8268 #>                              PH p_value #> data[[status_vacc_col]]v reject 0.00805

what: Function to construct the inmunization date — get_immunization_date
title: Function to construct the inmunization date — get_immunization_date
text: function returns column immunization date corresponds analysed outcome. register presents outcome, function search closest vaccine date outcome satisfies condition: vacc_date_col <= outcome_date_col - delay_time - immunization_delay. condition allows discriminate vaccine dates terms characteristic times days (delay_time)  associated outcome, onset symptoms reference event, characteristic time days patient considered immune (immunization_delay). parameters can set zero user without affecting results. register present outcome, immunization date can construct using closest vaccine date end study (take_first = FALSE), first vaccination date found (take_first = TRUE). Notice function works one several vaccines. case several vaccines, parameter outcome_date_col must passed vector (see example)

title: Function to construct the inmunization date — get_immunization_date
code: get_immunization_date(   data,   outcome_date_col,   outcome_delay,   immunization_delay,   vacc_date_col,   end_cohort,   take_first = TRUE )

title: Function to construct the inmunization date — get_immunization_date
text: data dataset cohort information (see example) outcome_date_col name column contains outcome dates outcome_delay characteristic time days outcome reference event immunization_delay characteristic time days patient considered immune vacc_date_col name column(s) contains vaccine dates end_cohort end date study take_first TRUE: takes minimum vaccine date registers without outcome. FALSE: takes closest end_cohort
